      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:9:12:7",
      "text": [
        " الْكِلَابُ السُّودُ الْبَهِيمُ مِنَ الْجِنِّ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "A number of our companions, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad, and Muhammad Bin yahya, from Abdullah Bin Muhammad, from Ali Bin Al Hakam, from Aban, from Zurara, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from one of the two (5<sup>th</sup> or 6<sup>th</sup> Imam<sup>asws</sup>) having said: ‘The dogs, entirely black, are from the Jinn’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "7. A number of our people have narrated from Ahmad ibn Muhammad from and Muhammad ibn Yahya from ‘Abd Allah ibn Muhammad from Ali ibn al-Hakam from Aban from Zurarah who has said the following: “One of the two Imam, (abu Ja‘far or abu ‘Abd Allah), ‘Alayhim al-Salam, has said that dogs of one color, all black are from Jinn.’” "
        ]
      }
